Bomb explosion at Kamjong on poll eve 
7-3-2017 
A powerful bomb exploded in Manipurâ€™s Kamjong district on Tuesday on the eve of the second phase of Manipur assembly poll when a patrol party of 31 Assam Rifles was on foot patrol duty,

Police said here the explosion took place at about 3.30 pm on Kongal-Aisi road and there was no report of injury in the explosion.

Kamjong district is one of those which will go to the polls for the Manipur assembly in the second phase tomoorw.

A large number of security forces rushed to the spot after the explosion but none was arrested till late evening, the police added. 
